
[1]rejoice

   REJOICE, v.i. rejois'.

   To experience joy and gladness in a high degree; to be exhilarated with
   lively and pleasurable sensations; to exult.

   When the righteous are in authority, the people rejoice; but when the
   wicked beareth rule, the people mourn. Prov. 29.

   I will rejoice in thy salvation. Ps. 9.

     REJOICE, v.t. rejois'. To make joyful; to gladden; to animate with
                lively pleasurable sensations; to exhilarate.

   Whoso loveth wisdom rejoiceth his father. Prov. 29.

   While she, great saint, rejoices heaven.
